definition.value: An amino hexasaccharide comprising alpha-L-fucosyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl, alpha-D-galactosyl, 6-azido-beta-D-galactosyl and (at the reducing end) beta-D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->2), (1->3), (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4). An azido-globo H analogue, it can be conjugated to the diphtheria toxoid cross-reactive material CRM197 for vaccination with C34 adjuvant in mice.
A tricyclic diterpenoid with formula C22H34O4. It is produced by the bird's nest fungus Cyathus earlei.
An L-cysteine derivative that is L-cysteine in which the thiol and amino groups are replaced by hydroxysulfanediyl and acetylamino groups, respectively.

An amino hexasaccharide derivative that is alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-beta-D-GalpNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-Galp6N3-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp (CHEBI:194350), the reducing-end residue of which is linked glycosidically to a 5-aminopentyl group linker.
An S-substituted N-acetyl-L-cysteinate that is the conjugate base of N-acetyl-S-phenyl-L-cysteine resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
